1. In plain language

  This Software is free for individuals, researchers, and for any organization's internal operations.

  A commercial license is only required if:

  (a) Revenue Trigger: Your organization’s Group Annual Revenue exceeds USD 100 million (inflation-adjusted from 2026) AND you use this Software for any external Software or services, OR
  (b) AI Trigger: You use this Software to train, run, or support AI models and services (including AI Agents and data generation) for any Software or services provided to external third parties, regardless of your revenue.

  Exception:
  
  * Migros Exception: Migros-Genossenschafts-Bund and its Affiliates are exempt from all commercial license requirements regardless of revenue, AI usage, or any other trigger.

  Clarifications:
  
  * Cloud Usage: It doesn’t matter where you run the Software. Hosting it on third-party infrastructure (like AWS or Azure) is always permitted for your own internal operations.

  * Consulting & Services: Using this Software as a tool to provide professional services or custom development for clients is free. However, if your client is a Commercial Software Entity and this Software becomes part of a product or service they offer to others, that client must obtain their own commercial license.

  If you are unsure whether you need a license, you almost certainly do not.

2. Definitions

  "Affiliate": Any entity that directly or indirectly controls, is controlled by, or is under common control with the licensee. "Control" means ownership of more than 50% of the voting interests or the power to direct the management and policies of an entity.

  "Group Annual Revenue": The total global revenue of the entity using this Software together with all of its Affiliates during the most recently completed fiscal year.

  "Revenue Threshold": USD 100,000,000 as of January 1, 2026, adjusted annually starting January 1, 2027, in accordance with the US Consumer Price Index for All Urban Consumers (CPI-U) published by the US Bureau of Labor Statistics.

  "Commercial Software Entity": Any organization (excluding Migros-Genossenschafts-Bund and its Affiliates) that meets two criteria:
  (a) Its Group Annual Revenue is at or above the Revenue Threshold; AND
  (b) It provides Software or Software-based services to external parties as part of its business.

  "Commercial Use": Any use of this Software where the Software, its source code, or any derived models are intended for, or contribute to, a product or service offered to external third parties. The mere delivery of static outputs (such as reports, generated data, or code snippets) as part of Professional Services does not constitute Commercial Use, provided the Software itself is not integrated into a client's Software.

  "Threshold Crossing": The point at which an entity's Group Annual Revenue first equals or exceeds the Revenue Threshold. Upon a Threshold Crossing, the entity enters a 90-day grace period during which it may continue to use this Software without a commercial license while obtaining one. Use of this Software for Commercial Use after expiry of the grace period without a valid commercial license constitutes a breach of Section 4.

  "Change of Control": Any transaction resulting in a change of the ultimate beneficial owner or controlling entity of a licensee, including merger, acquisition, or asset purchase.

  "European Entity": An entity directly entering into this license that is headquartered in the EEA or Switzerland, provided its ultimate parent company is also located within these territories.

  "AI Agent": An automated system generating or submitting code without direct, line-by-line human review and manual submission.

  "AI & Model Usage": Using this Software—including its source code, documentation, or outputs—to train, fine-tune, operate, or support AI models, AI agents, or autonomous systems (including data generation and RAG) intended for or contributing to a service offered to external parties.

3. Grant of Rights

  Subject to Section 4, you are granted a worldwide, royalty-free license to use, copy, modify, and distribute this Software and derivatives for any purpose.

4. Limitation

  No person or entity may engage in Commercial Use of this Software without a valid commercial license if:

  (a) they are a Commercial Software Entity; OR
  (b) the Commercial Use involves AI & Model Usage, regardless of the entity's revenue.

  This restriction applies to the entity's entire group, regardless of which member of the group performs the Commercial Use. No person or entity subject to this restriction may avoid this restriction by:

  (i) causing a subsidiary, affiliate, or newly formed entity to perform Commercial Use on its behalf;
  (ii) acquiring a licensee in order to inherit that licensee's license without obtaining a new commercial license covering the enlarged group;
  (iii) interposing any intermediary to obscure the ultimate beneficial use.

  Any commercial license granted under this License terminates automatically and immediately upon a Change of Control that results in the licensee becoming part of a group that does not hold a valid commercial license covering the enlarged group. The new controlling entity must obtain a commercial license immediately; failure to do so constitutes a breach of this Section retroactively from the date of the Change of Control.

  Notwithstanding the above, Migros-Genossenschafts-Bund and its Affiliates shall not be considered a Commercial Software Entity under this License and are exempt from the restrictions set forth in this Section 4.

